3
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:46,743
[Episode 8] Come on!

4
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:48,243
Dad.

5
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:50,276
Excuse me, teachers.

6
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:55,143
We have a new driver
for our shuttle bus from now on.

7
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:57,300
Mr. Gil, come over here for a second.

8
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:02,376
Please take a moment to greet them.

9
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,033
Oh, my.

10
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:09,010
Pleased to meet you.

11
00:01:09,034 --> 00:01:11,909
My name is Gil Ho Se.

12
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:13,909
- Hello.
- Hello.

13
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:17,176
Let's all work well together this month.

14
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,609
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

15
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:21,443
Was it difficult to memorize
the children's addresses?

16
00:01:21,467 --> 00:01:23,700
No, that's part of my job.

17
00:01:25,967 --> 00:01:28,076
Please take good care of
the afternoon drop-offs too.

18
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:29,733
Yes, Principal.

19
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:32,543
- Let's go in.
- Let's go.

20
00:01:32,567 --> 00:01:36,567
A thief has appeared! Catch the thief!

21
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:40,043
Principal.

22
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:41,700
Yes.

23
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:45,843
How did you find Mr. Gil Ho Se?

24
00:01:45,867 --> 00:01:47,343
From a job recruitment site.

25
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:50,909
Before his leg injury, he worked
at several transport companies.

26
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:53,276
Could I see his resume?

27
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,309
Why?

28
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,300
Does something seem off?

29
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,109
He's a stranger.

30
00:02:00,133 --> 00:02:01,843
I'm concerned about my
identity being exposed.

31
00:02:01,867 --> 00:02:03,709
Oh, my.

32
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:05,509
I hadn't considered that.

33
00:02:05,533 --> 00:02:08,033
Let's go. It's in the principal's office.

34
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:16,909
Here it is.

35
00:02:16,933 --> 00:02:20,976
I'll go teach the class,
so take your time checking.

36
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,767
- Okay.
- Okay.

37
00:02:30,112 --> 00:02:31,443
[Daehwang Transport]

38
00:02:31,467 --> 00:02:33,700
Daehwang Transport.

39
00:02:37,267 --> 00:02:39,376
Hello, this is the
Daehwang Transport office.

40
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:44,009
I'd like to check the background
of someone who worked there before.

41
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:45,643
His name is Gil Ho Se.

42
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:48,943
We keep records for only five years.

43
00:02:48,967 --> 00:02:51,643
If he worked here before that,
it would be difficult to verify.

44
00:02:51,667 --> 00:02:54,143
[Daehwang Transport 2015.10-2018.11]
What was his employment period?

45
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:56,676
[Work History] Ah, seven years ago.

46
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:59,100
Okay, I understand, thank you.

47
00:03:08,033 --> 00:03:12,243
Sorry, I thought the principal was here.

48
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:13,976
How can I help you?

49
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,909
Oh, the vehicle needs its
scheduled maintenance.

50
00:03:17,933 --> 00:03:21,509
So, I need to get it done
before the afternoon drop-offs.

51
00:03:21,533 --> 00:03:23,176
I'll let the principal know.

52
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:26,776
Oh, thank you.

53
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,200
- Thank you for your hard work.
- Oh, okay.

54
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,300
[Geumcheon Labor] Hurry up!

55
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,976
Captain.

56
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,909
That person over there.
I've never seen him before.

57
00:03:51,933 --> 00:03:53,176
Is he a total newbie?

58
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,643
Oh, him?

59
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:57,376
It's his first time here,
but he's worked many other places.

60
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,033
Try giving him a task, see how he does.

61
00:04:02,067 --> 00:04:03,609
If he can't handle it,

62
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:05,243
he'll be out right away, you know?

63
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:08,276
By the way, what's going on
with the Silver Town construction?

64
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:10,109
We need to get it done
so we can make a living.

65
00:04:10,133 --> 00:04:11,843
Ugh, just wait a bit.

66
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:14,743
That's giving me headaches too.

67
00:04:14,767 --> 00:04:17,543
But I'm going to wrap
it up before this winter.

68
00:04:17,567 --> 00:04:19,733
- I'm counting on you.
- Yes.

69
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,500
So exciting.

70
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:29,409
Ms. Bu, are you going with us today?

71
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:31,176
Yeah, I'm the one dropping them off today.

72
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,643
Oh, okay.

73
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:34,343
I'll close the door.

74
00:04:34,367 --> 00:04:35,576
I love it most.

75
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,243
- Me too.
- Absolutely love it.

76
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:40,343
Oh? Ms. Bu Se Mi's sitting in front of me.

77
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:42,209
Ms. Bu Se Mi's sitting next to me.

78
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:45,309
- I'm riding with Ms. Bu.
- But aren't you sitting in the back?

79
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:46,976
Today is great.

80
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,709
Alright, everyone.

81
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:51,009
Shall we sing our
kindergarten song together?

82
00:04:51,033 --> 00:04:52,509
- Yes.
- Yes.

83
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:55,876
- Start.
- S, s, start.

84
00:04:55,900 --> 00:05:02,076
♪ Embracing the green energy of the
mountains, our Muchang Iseon Kindergarten ♪

85
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:06,633
[Muchang Supermarket]

86
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:14,709
- Bye.
- See you tomorrow.

87
00:05:14,733 --> 00:05:17,667
- Bye-bye.
- See you.

88
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,009
Hae Na's mom.

89
00:05:20,033 --> 00:05:22,400
Mom, I'm home.

90
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,509
Huh? Oh.

91
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:33,009
You came today, huh?

92
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:35,433
Ms. Jenny has a lot of work to do.

93
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,533
I haven't seen those people before, right?

94
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:44,276
It's the busy season, so
Seong Tae brought them.

95
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:46,509
There's a shortage of
workers in the countryside.

96
00:05:46,533 --> 00:05:48,009
It must be a lot of work.

97
00:05:48,033 --> 00:05:50,000
I'll go now.

98
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:52,976
Goodbye.

99
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,276
Thank you. Miss, goodbye.

100
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,900
- Take care.
- Okay.

101
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:08,400
Ju Won's house is the last one.

102
00:06:09,233 --> 00:06:12,209
Mr. Gil, I'll get off with Ju Won this time.

103
00:06:12,233 --> 00:06:13,343
Oh, you too?

104
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:16,209
- Yes.
- She lives with us.

105
00:06:16,233 --> 00:06:17,976
Ah, really?

106
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,767
Wow, Ju Won. It must be nice.

107
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:29,000
We've arrived.

108
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:33,976
Alright, we've arrived.

109
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,867
Ju Won, let's go home.

110
00:06:38,267 --> 00:06:39,243
Let's go.

111
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:40,244
Thank you.

112
00:06:40,268 --> 00:06:41,509
Yes, Miss. Goodbye.

113
00:06:41,533 --> 00:06:42,876
See you tomorrow, Ju Won.

114
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:44,533
Yes.

115
00:06:47,067 --> 00:06:48,543
- Bye.
- See you.

116
00:06:48,567 --> 00:06:50,200
Yes.

117
00:07:01,367 --> 00:07:02,476
Ju Won, let's go.

118
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,143
Yes.

119
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:05,643
[Psychopath]

120
00:07:05,667 --> 00:07:07,800
She didn't even check the message.

121
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:14,967
That woman's all talk, isn't she?

122
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:35,933
That money from my
daughter is all my money.

123
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:54,309
Yeong Ran.

124
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:58,643
You're going to inherit that old man,
Chairman Ga Sung Ho's wealth, right?

125
00:07:58,667 --> 00:08:00,543
I've thought about it.

126
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:05,009
And how about 10 million won a month,
on the condition that I stay quiet?

127
00:08:05,033 --> 00:08:08,643
I looked it up online,
and that old man has a ton of assets.

128
00:08:08,667 --> 00:08:11,476
If we're talking about
10 million won a month

129
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:15,409
for the maintenance of Chairman Ga Sung Ho's
mother-in-law's dignity, that's a real bargain.

130
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:17,033
Don't you agree?

131
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:21,800
I'll give you a week.

132
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:25,300
Think carefully.

133
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:29,367
Yeong Ran.

134
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:43,100
Lee Don seems to be playing games.

135
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:52,500
[Seon Woo]

136
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,476
How long has he been holed up in the hotel?

137
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:04,133
Sis, it's me.

138
00:09:05,933 --> 00:09:08,143
Seon Woo.

139
00:09:08,167 --> 00:09:09,476
Where are you right now?

140
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:12,143
Shut up now and listen carefully.

141
00:09:12,167 --> 00:09:15,376
About those shares you have,

142
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,776
transfer all of them to me.

143
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:20,500
What does that even mean?

144
00:09:21,133 --> 00:09:22,843
'What does that even mean?'

145
00:09:22,867 --> 00:09:27,033
Don't pretend you don't know, again!

146
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,300
Don't you remember that day?

147
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:35,309
The day Ye Rim died.

148
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:37,733
You were in New York, right?

149
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:41,843
Well.

150
00:09:41,867 --> 00:09:45,033
I happen to have a video from that day.

151
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,167
Seon Woo.

152
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:52,909
Let's meet and talk.

153
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:53,910
How about it?

154
00:09:53,934 --> 00:09:58,609
If you accept my offer, come to Suite 858,
Sujeong Hotel, right now.

155
00:09:58,633 --> 00:10:00,933
If you refuse my offer,

156
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:03,843
I'll just send this to Kim Yeong Ran.

157
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:05,500
Do as you will.

158
00:10:11,933 --> 00:10:16,733
[Seon Woo]

159
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:29,033
Wow... These siblings, really...

160
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:35,443
Seon Woo is in Suite 858 at Sujeong Hotel.

161
00:10:35,467 --> 00:10:38,576
No matter what it takes,
bring him to me right now.

162
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,267
Yes, Professor.

163
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:48,100
[Ms. Bu Se Mi]

164
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:53,633
[Gil Ho Se's Resume]

165
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,509
Yes?

166
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:00,643
Madam.

167
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:03,776
Ga Seon Woo has decisive evidence

168
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,143
that Ga Seon Yeong is
involved in Ye Rim's death.

169
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:06,909
Is that evidence reliable?

170
00:11:06,933 --> 00:11:09,509
Yes, I've verified it.

171
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:11,243
If we secure this evidence,

172
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:14,676
this game will end quickly
without any bloodshed.

173
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:15,943
Yes, understood.

174
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:18,343
For now, please secure
the evidence, Attorney Lee.

175
00:11:18,367 --> 00:11:22,309
But I'll follow through
on the promise I made to Chairman.

176
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:23,609
Understood, Madam.

177
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:26,743
Things are turning in our favor,

178
00:11:26,767 --> 00:11:29,600
so please stay alive.

179
00:12:04,567 --> 00:12:06,333
What's with the bouquet?

180
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:11,276
- Is it for confession?
- Be quiet.

181
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,900
Oh, jeez.

182
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:17,209
Where is she rushing off to?

183
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:20,076
Hey, I've got an emergency. I'll be back.

184
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:21,876
Good luck with your confession.

185
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:23,633
Dong Min, hey.

186
00:12:34,267 --> 00:12:36,067
Where did she go?

187
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:43,076
Corn.

188
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,576
When the corn grows tall, tall, tall,

189
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,709
pick the corn, knock, knock, knock,

190
00:12:47,733 --> 00:12:49,843
peel off the husk, shuck, shuck, shuck,

191
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:51,909
then the corn is plump, plump, plump!

192
00:12:51,933 --> 00:12:53,309
You startled me.

193
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:55,109
Ms. Baek Hye Ji.

194
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,176
Make some noise when you walk!

195
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,709
I'm the owner of this house,

196
00:12:58,733 --> 00:13:01,933
yet I feel like a squatter in my own home.

197
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,843
Oh, what a scare.

198
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:10,076
Nobody here is normal, including Madam.

199
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:11,309
Ugh, what should I do?

200
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:14,253
[Practical Assignment for 'Field Practice']
I need to upload this quickly.

201
00:13:21,333 --> 00:13:23,700
The moon today

202
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:27,067
is dark tonight.

203
00:14:42,467 --> 00:14:43,843
Who are you?

204
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:45,500
Answer me!

205
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,533
Miss.

206
00:15:03,533 --> 00:15:05,109
Are you okay?

207
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:06,767
There...

208
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:27,009
He disappeared near here, right?

209
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:28,633
Yes.

210
00:15:29,733 --> 00:15:31,076
By the way, where are we?

211
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,576
It's the lodging for the farmhands.

212
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,509
I think the only place
he could run to is here.

213
00:15:34,533 --> 00:15:35,643
I'll go check it out.

214
00:15:35,667 --> 00:15:36,909
Oh, wait a minute.

215
00:15:36,933 --> 00:15:38,176
This is the men's lodging.

216
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,833
I'll go check. Wait here for a bit.

217
00:15:44,633 --> 00:15:47,343
No, that's not it.

218
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:49,067
It's not.

219
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:14,643
Who are you looking for?

220
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:17,300
Oh, nothing.

221
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:33,576
There is someone suspicious, though.

222
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,109
It's late today,

223
00:16:35,133 --> 00:16:37,209
so I'll check with Seong Tae tomorrow.

224
00:16:37,233 --> 00:16:39,076
Let's call it a day for now.

225
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,943
That person had a scar on their collarbone.

226
00:16:40,967 --> 00:16:42,909
It would be useful if
you remembered that too.

227
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:45,276
A scar on the collarbone...

228
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:46,933
Got it.

229
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:49,509
Wait.

230
00:16:49,533 --> 00:16:51,233
Give me your phone.

231
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,643
My phone?

232
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:55,509
Why do you need my phone?

233
00:16:55,533 --> 00:16:58,467
How am I saved in your contacts?

234
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,243
Jeon Dong Min.

235
00:17:01,267 --> 00:17:03,100
Jeon Dong Min?

236
00:17:04,367 --> 00:17:07,476
Not Mr. Jeon Dong Min,
not Mr. Jeon, not Teacher.

237
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,543
You really typed it honestly, huh?

238
00:17:10,567 --> 00:17:14,109
I set up a speed dial for you.

239
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:16,509
If there's an emergency, just press 1.

240
00:17:16,533 --> 00:17:19,133
I'll get there faster than the police, okay?

241
00:17:19,933 --> 00:17:22,333
No need for this stuff.

242
00:17:27,733 --> 00:17:30,700
Wow, her personality is something else.

243
00:17:49,933 --> 00:17:51,833
Tae Min, what are you doing there?

244
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:02,000
Oh, this, this thing.

245
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:06,767
The one you mentioned last time.

246
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,376
Tae Min.

247
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,000
Yes.

248
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:16,543
You like me, right?

249
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:18,333
Well.

250
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,867
Oh, that's...

251
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:25,243
Oh, wait.

252
00:18:25,267 --> 00:18:26,343
No.

253
00:18:26,367 --> 00:18:30,533
No, not now. No.

254
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:41,867
Baek Hye Ji.

255
00:18:42,533 --> 00:18:44,167
Yes.

256
00:18:48,967 --> 00:18:53,800
I admire her.

257
00:18:58,733 --> 00:18:59,943
General.

258
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:01,667
Why?

259
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:05,833
People don't confess like that these days.

260
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:08,476
It's old-fashioned.

261
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:10,333
Old-fashioned?

262
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:14,643
I don't care about what's trendy.

263
00:19:14,667 --> 00:19:18,576
Tae Min's been worried sick about you.

264
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,767
Just remember that.

265
00:19:30,533 --> 00:19:31,809
This...

266
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:34,067
Huh? General.

267
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:36,743
- Tae Min.
- Yes.

268
00:19:36,767 --> 00:19:40,000
I'm tired. I'm going inside.

269
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:44,209
Wait.

270
00:19:44,233 --> 00:19:46,543
General! General!

271
00:19:46,567 --> 00:19:49,443
Please, was that a confession or not?

272
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:52,533
What do I do?

273
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:05,667
Mom.

274
00:21:21,728 --> 00:21:23,709
[Answer, Door Open]

275
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:26,633
Ugh, where are they?

276
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,800
Why aren't they here yet?

277
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:52,533
I knew Ga Seon Yeong wouldn't come herself.

278
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:56,567
I can't let Ga Seon Woo get caught.

279
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:03,533
Vice President.

280
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:07,976
Open the door!

281
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,767
Vice President.

282
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:15,376
[Answer, Door Open] Open up.

283
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,000
What?

284
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,867
Only Secretary Han came?

285
00:22:20,864 --> 00:22:22,795
Shoot!

286
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:25,143
Yeah.

287
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:28,443
My sister always does this.

288
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:31,633
You think I don't know you're trying to
lock me up and kill me like Dad?

289
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:36,233
Come out.

290
00:22:39,667 --> 00:22:41,400
Vice President.

291
00:22:43,933 --> 00:22:45,667
Come out.

292
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,709
Vice President.

293
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:55,709
Come out.

294
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:57,333
Huh?

295
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,633
Vice President.

296
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:13,200
Vice President.

297
00:23:26,272 --> 00:23:29,432
Excuse me, let me get it for you.

298
00:23:34,467 --> 00:23:35,876
- Fire!
- Fire!

299
00:23:35,900 --> 00:23:37,043
Fire, fire!

300
00:23:37,067 --> 00:23:38,576
- Fire, fire!
- Get away from the fire.

301
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:41,933
Get away from the fire.

302
00:23:43,333 --> 00:23:44,967
Go that way.

303
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,533
Fire!

304
00:23:57,376 --> 00:24:00,409
- Darn. Get out quickly!
- Oh, no.

305
00:24:00,433 --> 00:24:02,033
Let's go.

306
00:24:08,967 --> 00:24:10,833
You want to give it a shot?

307
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:14,833
I'm not going to sit still anymore.

308
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:47,809
What is that?

309
00:24:47,833 --> 00:24:49,476
It's a list of today's tasks.

310
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:51,009
First, let's go to Seong Tae,

311
00:24:51,033 --> 00:24:55,343
get information about people
who came from outside.

312
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:57,009
Okay.

313
00:24:57,033 --> 00:24:58,476
About that guy from yesterday.

314
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:00,743
You mentioned he had a scar
on his collarbone, right?

315
00:25:00,767 --> 00:25:02,500
Which side was it on?

316
00:25:03,767 --> 00:25:05,143
Who are you?

317
00:25:05,144 --> 00:25:25,144
Officail Website : kissasian.be  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

318
00:25:05,167 --> 00:25:06,867
Answer me!

319
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:10,909
- The left.
- Left.

320
00:25:10,933 --> 00:25:14,267
A scar on the left collarbone.

321
00:25:15,367 --> 00:25:18,143
Probably someone athletic.

322
00:25:18,167 --> 00:25:19,876
I'll keep a close eye out.

323
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:21,500
Let's go.

324
00:25:25,433 --> 00:25:27,943
We need to do it as soon as possible.

325
00:25:27,967 --> 00:25:29,309
Okay?

326
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:30,310
Seong Tae.

327
00:25:30,334 --> 00:25:31,909
It's just that I heard from someone

328
00:25:31,933 --> 00:25:35,643
that your people have a great reputation
for doing good work.

329
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:36,709
They really are good.

330
00:25:36,733 --> 00:25:38,609
So, by the way,

331
00:25:38,633 --> 00:25:42,700
if you have any contact details or personal
info, could you share them with me?

332
00:25:44,433 --> 00:25:46,609
You're just asking for that?

333
00:25:46,633 --> 00:25:49,209
By the way, Hae Na left
her pencil case yesterday.

334
00:25:49,233 --> 00:25:52,276
I was thinking of dropping it off
when I head to the supermarket.

335
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:54,767
I'll text you right away.

336
00:25:56,467 --> 00:25:58,809
Hurry up, come on.

337
00:25:58,833 --> 00:26:01,876
Oh, not bad at all.

338
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:03,509
We should split up here.

339
00:26:03,533 --> 00:26:04,543
What?

340
00:26:04,567 --> 00:26:06,109
We just teamed up, and
you're already leaving?

341
00:26:06,133 --> 00:26:07,476
I have to get to work.

342
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:09,343
Oh, right.

343
00:26:09,367 --> 00:26:13,100
Since I'm free, I'll look around a bit more.

344
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,143
Hello.

345
00:26:16,167 --> 00:26:17,409
Excuse me, by any chance,

346
00:26:17,433 --> 00:26:19,409
is there anyone here

347
00:26:19,433 --> 00:26:21,409
who has a scar on their collarbone?

348
00:26:21,433 --> 00:26:24,843
Someone with a dark face and a tall build?

349
00:26:24,867 --> 00:26:26,509
Have you worked with
anyone like that before?

350
00:26:26,533 --> 00:26:27,776
No.

351
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:29,467
Thank you.

352
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,376
Jeong Woo!

353
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,909
Oh, Dong Min.

354
00:26:34,933 --> 00:26:36,209
[Muchang Police Station]
What brings you here so early?

355
00:26:36,233 --> 00:26:37,243
Hello.

356
00:26:37,267 --> 00:26:39,176
Well, actually,

357
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:41,043
I was walking last night

358
00:26:41,067 --> 00:26:44,243
and saw a suspicious person
lurking at the village entrance.

359
00:26:44,267 --> 00:26:46,243
Oh really? Why didn't you report it?

360
00:26:46,267 --> 00:26:48,143
Please do more night patrols.

361
00:26:48,167 --> 00:26:51,176
Got it, got it. We'll step up patrols.
(Watch on www.kisskh, la to support Admin)

362
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,243
Keep up the good work.

363
00:26:52,267 --> 00:26:53,943
- Yes.
- Bye.

364
00:26:53,967 --> 00:26:57,733
Let's keep up our night patrols.

365
00:26:59,933 --> 00:27:04,533
Patrols are stronger, list is ready.

366
00:27:05,267 --> 00:27:08,633
Now, I just need to protect Ms. Bu Se Mi.

367
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:24,509
Miss.

368
00:27:24,533 --> 00:27:26,676
There's a guy named Lee Se Joon here.

369
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:29,043
He works night shifts every day.

370
00:27:29,067 --> 00:27:31,543
We should check him out.

371
00:27:31,567 --> 00:27:33,209
Okay.

372
00:27:33,233 --> 00:27:36,433
Stay here. I'll go investigate.

373
00:28:07,667 --> 00:28:09,300
Miss!

374
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,509
Where are you?

375
00:28:16,533 --> 00:28:18,509
He just went into Muchang
Supermarket Alley.

376
00:28:18,533 --> 00:28:20,076
I think it's him.

377
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:22,100
Got it, I'm on my way.

378
00:29:03,833 --> 00:29:05,867
Darn it.

379
00:29:25,533 --> 00:29:27,133
Get up.

380
00:29:28,867 --> 00:29:30,543
It hurts.

381
00:29:30,567 --> 00:29:31,976
He has no scar.

382
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:33,943
Hey, what's wrong with you guys?

383
00:29:33,967 --> 00:29:35,009
It's you, right?

384
00:29:35,033 --> 00:29:36,509
You were the one who
attacked her yesterday, right?

385
00:29:36,533 --> 00:29:38,509
What are you talking about?

386
00:29:38,533 --> 00:29:41,067
Didn't you break the CCTV?

387
00:29:42,567 --> 00:29:44,543
I heard they were hiring at Mu Si Market,

388
00:29:44,567 --> 00:29:47,376
I just did what I was
told and got paid for it.

389
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:49,943
Man, I knew something was off.

390
00:29:49,967 --> 00:29:51,676
Does that person limp?

391
00:29:51,700 --> 00:29:53,743
We only communicated via phone.

392
00:29:53,767 --> 00:29:56,176
I don't know anything about him.

393
00:29:56,200 --> 00:30:00,109
I just did what they told me, they said
I'd get 50,000 for each CCTV I broke,

394
00:30:00,133 --> 00:30:02,509
so I worked hard for it.

395
00:30:02,533 --> 00:30:05,067
Then how did you know the CCTV routes?

396
00:30:08,733 --> 00:30:10,676
That guy sent me all the details.

397
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:12,609
Including all the patrol routes.

398
00:30:12,633 --> 00:30:18,333
[Mu Si Market]

399
00:30:53,767 --> 00:30:56,209
Wow, he's fast.

400
00:30:56,233 --> 00:30:57,943
Ah, we lost him.

401
00:30:57,967 --> 00:30:59,576
By the way, earlier,

402
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:02,643
you asked if he was limping, right?

403
00:31:02,667 --> 00:31:05,509
Are you talking about that driver?

404
00:31:05,533 --> 00:31:06,743
Yes.

405
00:31:06,767 --> 00:31:08,776
The only recent newcomers to Muchang

406
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:11,709
are the driver and seasonal farm workers.

407
00:31:11,733 --> 00:31:13,333
That's right.

408
00:31:14,467 --> 00:31:17,976
Hey, let's call it a day.

409
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,633
Okay.

410
00:31:26,367 --> 00:31:28,076
[Gil Ho Se's Resume]
Why hasn't he checked this?

411
00:31:28,100 --> 00:31:30,733
[Attorney Lee]

412
00:31:32,733 --> 00:31:37,500
The subscriber you dialed is unavailable.
You will be connected to voicemail.

413
00:31:52,367 --> 00:31:54,509
Who the heck are you guys?

414
00:31:54,533 --> 00:31:55,709
Hey.

415
00:31:55,733 --> 00:31:57,467
Where's Ga Seon Woo?

416
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:00,743
That's what I want to know.

417
00:32:00,767 --> 00:32:03,909
Ah, that lunatic.

418
00:32:03,933 --> 00:32:06,309
Boss, what about our money?

419
00:32:06,333 --> 00:32:08,833
Do you know who I am?

420
00:32:09,767 --> 00:32:11,843
Attorney Lee Don.

421
00:32:11,867 --> 00:32:15,309
We're not in the mood for games.

422
00:32:15,333 --> 00:32:16,709
Why?

423
00:32:16,733 --> 00:32:18,576
Did Ga Seon Woo rip you off?

424
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:20,676
You punk.

425
00:32:20,700 --> 00:32:23,643
People are all talking down to me.

426
00:32:23,667 --> 00:32:26,343
I'll give you all the money
Ga Seon Woo owes.

427
00:32:26,367 --> 00:32:28,600
I'm loaded.

428
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:36,233
But why should we trust you?

429
00:32:36,933 --> 00:32:39,443
How did you find me?

430
00:32:39,467 --> 00:32:41,376
That's our specialty.

431
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:42,976
Really?

432
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:45,500
I'm looking for Ga Seon Woo too.

433
00:32:46,933 --> 00:32:49,209
100 million if you find Ga Seon Woo.

434
00:32:49,233 --> 00:32:52,600
Until then10 million deduction daily. Deal?

435
00:32:54,267 --> 00:32:56,009
Ah, this is frustrating.

436
00:32:56,033 --> 00:32:58,433
Another day's already passing.

437
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:04,009
Are you joking, punk?

438
00:33:04,033 --> 00:33:06,376
Soon, 10 million won will be deducted.

439
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:08,033
Pay the deposit of 50 million won.

440
00:33:09,033 --> 00:33:10,833
I got it, so let me go.

441
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:14,633
Hey.

442
00:33:25,300 --> 00:33:27,067
50 million won for the deposit.

443
00:33:30,133 --> 00:33:31,767
Transfer it.

444
00:33:36,467 --> 00:33:37,843
[Ms. Bu Se Mi]

445
00:33:37,867 --> 00:33:39,667
[Gil Ho Se's Resume]

446
00:33:41,567 --> 00:33:43,509
[Shuttle Bus Driver]

447
00:33:43,533 --> 00:33:47,109
[Mid-40s, had an
accident and injured his leg]

448
00:33:47,133 --> 00:33:49,900
[Gil Ho Se]

449
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:56,767
Can you find another person?

450
00:33:58,567 --> 00:34:00,309
An additional 100 million won.

451
00:34:00,333 --> 00:34:02,376
Same terms.

452
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:04,033
Deal.

453
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:06,800
Transfer it.

454
00:34:19,633 --> 00:34:21,567
Come this way.

455
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:33,309
I heard you do a great job here, so I came.

456
00:34:33,333 --> 00:34:35,433
I need a passport.

457
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:38,043
How long does it take?

458
00:34:38,067 --> 00:34:40,476
Passport takes 3 days.

459
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:43,109
It's not available for the U.S. or Europe,

460
00:34:43,133 --> 00:34:44,676
but no problem for Southeast Asia.

461
00:34:44,700 --> 00:34:47,476
No problem with money,

462
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:50,276
so the faster, the better.

463
00:34:50,300 --> 00:34:53,300
Rushing leads to mistakes.

464
00:34:58,233 --> 00:34:59,876
I said I got it.

465
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:01,733
Just meet the deadline.

466
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,700
Come back in 3 days.

467
00:35:14,567 --> 00:35:17,943
Ms. Bu Se Mi, there's an announcement.

468
00:35:17,967 --> 00:35:22,009
This week, a village volleyball competition will
be held at the elementary school playground.

469
00:35:22,033 --> 00:35:23,443
Please attend.

470
00:35:23,467 --> 00:35:24,709
There's an after-party too.

471
00:35:24,733 --> 00:35:27,376
Let's celebrate together and have dinner.

472
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:28,976
- Principal.
- Yes?

473
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:31,576
Are there people coming
from other villages?

474
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,476
Well,

475
00:35:33,500 --> 00:35:35,343
Dong Min and Jeong Woo from YBS,

476
00:35:35,367 --> 00:35:37,909
and Dongwaru and upper
village chief from OBS.

477
00:35:37,933 --> 00:35:40,376
Mainly upper village folks.

478
00:35:40,400 --> 00:35:41,976
Got it.

479
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:43,600
Yes.

480
00:35:44,567 --> 00:35:45,976
Good morning, Principal.

481
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,133
Good morning.

482
00:35:51,767 --> 00:35:53,433
Ms. Baek Hye Ji.

483
00:35:54,433 --> 00:35:56,643
Let's talk for a minute.

484
00:35:56,667 --> 00:35:59,500
I need to prepare materials before class.

485
00:36:00,733 --> 00:36:03,367
I'll come to Strawberry Class after class.

486
00:36:04,100 --> 00:36:06,467
Have a good class.

487
00:36:08,433 --> 00:36:10,033
Don't worry.

488
00:36:11,367 --> 00:36:13,033
See you then.

489
00:36:15,167 --> 00:36:17,376
Okay.

490
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:18,676
Gimme a bite.

491
00:36:18,700 --> 00:36:20,443
- No.
- Just one bite.

492
00:36:20,467 --> 00:36:23,243
- No, I'll eat it all.
- One bite.

493
00:36:23,267 --> 00:36:25,100
Just one bite.

494
00:36:26,767 --> 00:36:29,509
Mister, I'm sorry.

495
00:36:29,533 --> 00:36:31,509
No, are you okay?

496
00:36:31,533 --> 00:36:32,609
I'm fine.

497
00:36:32,633 --> 00:36:35,243
I can change clothes, so it's fine.

498
00:36:35,267 --> 00:36:36,743
Oh, no.

499
00:36:36,767 --> 00:36:38,143
Oh, you spilled it.

500
00:36:38,167 --> 00:36:40,843
Running's dangerous, right?

501
00:36:40,867 --> 00:36:42,243
Let's go in.

502
00:36:42,267 --> 00:36:44,600
Go inside and play.

503
00:37:53,700 --> 00:37:55,600
You got me.

504
00:37:56,467 --> 00:37:59,167
Now, you recognize my footsteps?

505
00:38:10,133 --> 00:38:11,709
Ms. Baek Hye Ji.

506
00:38:11,733 --> 00:38:13,909
Why did you follow me last night?

507
00:38:13,933 --> 00:38:15,667
Are you spying on me?

508
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:22,033
Yes.

509
00:38:22,767 --> 00:38:24,700
I'm spying on you.

510
00:38:30,833 --> 00:38:33,143
I won't ask who told you to do this,

511
00:38:33,167 --> 00:38:36,243
but now stop playing
games and leave Muchang.

512
00:38:36,267 --> 00:38:39,233
I don't want to care
about you anymore either.

513
00:38:39,933 --> 00:38:41,533
Please.

514
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:28,676
Oh, it's Hye Ji.

515
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:29,709
[Baek Hye Ji]

516
00:39:29,733 --> 00:39:32,000
Call me in 30 minutes.

517
00:39:39,467 --> 00:39:41,543
Yes, Miss.

518
00:39:41,567 --> 00:39:43,109
Are you heading home?

519
00:39:43,133 --> 00:39:44,110
Yes.

520
00:39:44,134 --> 00:39:46,743
Then, please give me a ride home.

521
00:39:46,767 --> 00:39:48,843
Sure, get in.

522
00:39:48,867 --> 00:39:50,700
- Thank you.
- Yes.

523
00:39:59,867 --> 00:40:03,333
Alright, let's go.

524
00:40:16,867 --> 00:40:18,867
Miss, what are you looking for?

525
00:40:20,100 --> 00:40:24,500
Well, I've always wondered about
the shuttle bus's front seats.

526
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:28,743
Nothing special.

527
00:40:28,767 --> 00:40:31,576
Where do you live, Mr. Gil?

528
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:33,833
Why ask that?

529
00:40:35,233 --> 00:40:40,243
Well, I came down here and have
been staying at the principal's place.

530
00:40:40,267 --> 00:40:42,300
I'm trying to find a place to live.

531
00:40:44,633 --> 00:40:47,709
But I just got a place
through someone I know.

532
00:40:47,733 --> 00:40:48,943
Oh?

533
00:40:48,967 --> 00:40:51,833
Do you know someone here? Who?

534
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:54,743
Well, I've met most people in this town
at the village welcome party,

535
00:40:54,767 --> 00:40:57,043
so I know everyone
in this neighborhood, more or less.

536
00:40:57,067 --> 00:40:58,976
Oh, I see.

537
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,700
Who is it?

538
00:41:03,067 --> 00:41:05,400
You really wanna know?

539
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:13,776
30, 29, 28, 27.

540
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:18,133
26, 25, 24, 23...

541
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:25,400
No way...

542
00:41:27,733 --> 00:41:29,333
Is it the village chief?

543
00:41:31,767 --> 00:41:33,576
It's the village chief.

544
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:34,976
Ah, right.

545
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:36,109
How did you know?

546
00:41:36,133 --> 00:41:40,443
Everything and everyone here

547
